  "text": "The Android rendering pipeline flows as follows: (1) View.java (core/java/android/view/View.java) defines the public measure() at line 28137 which delegates to onMeasure() at line 28269, layout() at line 25385 delegating to onLayout() at line 25502, and draw() at line 24849 delegating to onDraw() at line 22298. (2) ViewRootImpl.java (core/java/android/view/ViewRootImpl.java) is the bridge between WindowManager and the view hierarchy \u2014 scheduleTraversals() at line 2948 posts a callback to Choreographer, and performTraversals() at line 3422 orchestrates the three phases via performMeasure() (line 4882), performLayout() (line 4948), and performDraw() (line 5348). (3) Choreographer.java (core/java/android/view/Choreographer.java) drives frame scheduling via VSYNC \u2014 postCallback() (line 491) and postFrameCallback() (line 613) schedule work, scheduleVsyncLocked() (line 1059) requests the next VSYNC signal, and doFrame() (line 853) dispatches all pending callbacks when VSYNC fires. (4) ThreadedRenderer.java (core/java/android/view/ThreadedRenderer.java, line 63) extends HardwareRenderer (graphics/java/android/graphics/HardwareRenderer.java, line 82) \u2014 its draw() method (line 795) calls updateRootDisplayList() (line 698) to record the view tree into a display list, then syncAndDrawFrame() (HardwareRenderer line 485) pushes the frame to the GPU render thread. (5) RecordingCanvas.java (graphics/java/android/graphics/RecordingCanvas.java, line 36) extends BaseRecordingCanvas (graphics/java/android/graphics/BaseRecordingCanvas.java) \u2014 this is the canvas that records draw operations into a RenderNode's display list for later GPU replay.",
